Hello people of delphi!

This is 3543’s first year operating with swerve and we are running into some difficulties getting the code to deploy. Currently we only have one module officially running and we wanted to test the drive. The problem is that our drivestation keeps giving us an error about the SwerveParser and the directories. We have solid connection and each time we delpoy the code, the little red light stays red. This is the error we are getting from our Rio:

posts.name: Ryan Blue
posts.cooked:
How are the encoders wired? Are they connected to the roborio or the spark max?

Mads_0927:

Invalid Index for Analog Input Status: -1030 Minimum: 0 Maximum: 8 Requested: 9

This error shows you have the code configured for encoders plugged into the analog inputs on the roborio, but you’ve used an invalid port number, 9 (there are only 8 analog inputs on the roborio, 0-4 on the analog input section, 5-7 on the mxp)

If they are connected to the roborio, make sure the port numbers in the configuration file match where the encoders are plugged in.

If they’re instead connected to the Spark MAX, you should use the sparkmax_analog encoder option.

posts.name: Mads <3
posts.cooked: The encoders attached to the motors come from the CAN Spark Max motor controllers. We have used them for the last 5 years. We also have 4 encoders attached to the modules and they are Thrifty encoder, but im not sure the exact type. Our Spark Max’s are id’s 1-8. None of our encoders are plugged directly into the roborio

Thrifty encoders are attached to the sparkmax so they are of the attached type. (Since they are dutycycle encoders attached to the SparkMAX)

If you are using the Thrifty encoders attached to the SparkMax (soldered lines to the data breakout board ) then you use sparkmax_analog (Correction below)
